			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>I think the term "taunt" is a misnomer for what is being asked for.&nbsp; To reinforce what othes are saying,&nbsp; I would be happy with the ability to re-gain agro within a reasonable amount of time, say 2 or 3&nbsp;ticks.&nbsp; Not exactly the snap agro that would make me a good main tank; but definately a usable ability to allow me to "pre-tank" a mob much the same way I "pre-slow" for shamen and&nbsp;"pre-mez" for enchanters.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Some people are saying this is unreasonable.&nbsp; How reasonable is it for a bard to HOS, slow, group buff and output 140ish dps for 3 or 4 ticks only to lose agro the second a chanter lands tash?&nbsp; Actually losing agro wouldn't be that bad, but it is almost embarassing to try and re-gain agro while said enchanter tanks the mob for the rest of the fight.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In my opinion, this fits in the bard genre of picking up the slack until the job gets filled by the appropriate class; or at least filling the job position albeit not as well.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
