									<p>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
										Viewed 260 times<br>
									</span>

									
									</td>

						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000>Fix our mitigation before you even consider giving us taunt. Honetly, I don't know what planet you I want taunt bards are coming from.</FONT></P>
<P>It's exactly your attitude I am astounded by mycrazytrain.&nbsp; I raised the initial post - go read it.&nbsp; Nowhere did I say that I wanted to take agro off tank classes, and from that perspective I agree with you 100%.&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000>Bards should never be an alternative to a warrior, SK or paladin tanking.&nbsp;</FONT> But why should rogues tank or rangers?&nbsp; Or monks, or beastlords?&nbsp; EVERY other melee class gets picked in an emergency except bards, and I've seen everyone of those classes offtank in Time.&nbsp; Yet bards wear plate armor.&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000>Shouldnt a plate wearer be a more likely tank than a leather class, or chain class?&nbsp; </FONT>Directly or indirectly those classes can get and maintain agro, yet a plate class cant.</P>
<P>Thats why I suggested it, and judging by the fact it got as many votes as it did I can only assume others agree.&nbsp; But the whole point is to not take tank duties off those that should have it, but to balance our abilities with those that tank when its not part of THEIR duties.&nbsp; Or have I missed something somewhere and chain and leather armor should be considered better for tanks than plate?</P>
<P>For me its as much a fight to be considered an equal as it is to balance, but in the modern homogenised game there is no reason bards SHOULDNT have some way to actively generate agro fast.&nbsp; And chain casting DoT's isnt a fast way.&nbsp; That's secondary to getting a plate class to the proper point in that chain of command though.</P></BLOCKQUOTE></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is exactly the reason bards should be an alternative to a warrior, SK, or Paladin.&nbsp; Clerics do it (depending on content being done).&nbsp; They were plate.&nbsp; Bards should be able to do the same.&nbsp; This is do to the fact that sometimes it is all about timing, and sometimes there are no tanks looking for a group.&nbsp; Instead rangers, beastlords, shamans or rogues are elected as main tanks.&nbsp; Other times it is the exact same situation except as off tanks instead of main tanks.&nbsp; There are two specific reasons why bards can't, and both reasons have been mentioned on all three bardic boards: mitigation and agro.&nbsp; I've had druids, chanters, and wizards play tank (via kiting) purely because of their ability to gain and hold agro once the MT fell.&nbsp; Now reread the last line again.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>How much agro generation would be enough?&nbsp; This is harder to answer, and truthfully most people would balk at the honest answer.&nbsp; The truth is bards should be able to generate a very high amount of agro.&nbsp; Why?&nbsp; Look at what any tank has to deal with in regards to gaining and keeping agro.&nbsp; Then look at the other classes agro is needed to be maintain to keep the agro off them.&nbsp; Most casting classes are very capable of stealing agro.&nbsp; Part of the learning a class is learning to control the agro generated in order to maintain the agro upon the main tank.&nbsp; The same should apply to the bard class as any other class.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The agro generated would have to be high enough to retain agro off the healers, off the shaman slowing, off the wizard dropping ONE nuke, off the chanter dropping tash, off the ranger or druid snaring, etc., etc., etc.&nbsp; Would it be enough to pull agro off a more viable MT?&nbsp; Yes, with varying degrees of difficulty.&nbsp; To give less would just be a gimped ability that wouldn't really be able to do any of the things it would really be used for as a lowest level plate classed&nbsp;melee tank or off tank when the situation arises.&nbsp; I'd rather just watch the raid or group wipe than get another broken ability.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Hand in hand the ability to gain and maintain agro when the need arises is the ability to better mitigate the damage taken.&nbsp; Whether bards would fall behind, on the same plataeu, or ahead of clerics I'll let others figure out.&nbsp; But bards should fall short of the other melee tanks while being ahead of the other classes.&nbsp; Otherwise it just winds up in the same gimped boat as agro would wind up in.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Being THE jack of all trades support class in EQ sometimes requires a bard to play the tank, at least it would if we were once again capable of doing so like we used to be able to do a long time ago.&nbsp; A bard is only picked when there isn't a better tank available.&nbsp; It happens, and far more frequently than some may think.&nbsp; In order to fill that role we need the abilities to do so.&nbsp; At present we lack them, hence other classes filling in those roles.&nbsp; This could also be considered a part of the utility problem also posted on.&nbsp; It is a utility roll bards started out with, and lost along the way, while other classes gained it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Polara Magami</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
