			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV>I think SOE cares a great deal, otherwise there is no point or reason to even listen to the player base at all.&nbsp; The fact that SOE is doing just that shows they do indead care.&nbsp; Why lower the agro from chants?&nbsp; Only SOE can answer this, and their general point is that they rarely explain a reason behind something.&nbsp; Just because the agro has been reduces doesn't mean SOE did it on purpose.&nbsp; It could be a bug.&nbsp; It could be that they are already addressing bard agro from the discussion list before it was actually even sent in, and altering chants was easier to do without requiring a lot of testing.&nbsp; The only response we are likely to get is if it was a bug.&nbsp; Which is pretty much what is stated in the original post regarding the comments about our first list items submitted.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This isn't an attack in any manner, shape, or form.&nbsp; I just disagree with your view of SOE not caring, so felt compelled to state otherwise, giving a couple of reasons why the agro generated from chants could or would be altered.&nbsp; Only time will tell if it is a bug or prep action for some other fix.&nbsp; I am willing to wait and see how it pans out.&nbsp; I still remember back in the days of old when bard songs were broken every other patch, and allowed to stay that way until the next patch.&nbsp; Nowadays SOE is just as apt to take the servers down to fix our songs as they are to fix major bugs with any other class.&nbsp; This too shows they care a great deal.&nbsp; I tip my hat to them on it too.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Polara Magami</DIV>
																		
