												<DIV>I'm a ranger and I just wanted to attempt to answer this.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Look up the early days of the ranger, our description as it was intended from the conception of EQ, we were described as a light tank. Even the description on this board says that we are "warriors attuned to the ways of nature". The general impression (from the original conception of classes) was that we were supposed to be 4th in the tank order. Now today, given the fact that we have substandard gear and skills to accomplish this as compared to the level of creatures we encounter at the high end does not nullify the fact that we were concieved as tanks (and hence why we got taunt). Rangers are still tanks, just not effective ones at high levels.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
																		
										</td></tr>
