						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												""""BARDS ARE A SUPPORT CLASS. We are not tanks. We do not tank. We do not need taunt."""""<br><br><br>Bards could be given taunt for the same reason that Druids, and shamans were given complete heal.  Sure, they're not nearly as good at it, and for most mobs you still wouldn't want one as a primary healer, but in a pinch they're a useful back-up if there is no one else available.<br><br>In order to "Step on" another classes role, you have to do their job at least equal to or better than they do.  Shadowknights and Paladin's hold agro better than warriors, even though they are not the "Prime" tank.  But warriors still mitigate better, making them a better choice in situtations where the incoming damage exceeds that which a Pal or SK can safely tank.  Even if a Bard can hold taunt, having mitigation/avoidance abilities even Sub-Par to Paladins, SK's, and even Monks(who get block) will still not make them a superior choice in any situtation to tank, and only a last-resort style choice.<br><br>Unfortunately, it doesn't really address any issues for Bards, as it doesn't really increase our desirability any in the Raid-level content area, which is the only area we're heavily lacking lately.  <br><br>The only thing this would do is Address issues for Casual gamers, who often have difficulties putting together a solid group and finding the classes needed.
																		
										</td></tr>
