			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>Wanted to say, that Tank mezzing belongs to Tanks. </FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000>Which bard is not. Plate class does not define a tank. Clerics are about as much tanks as Bards are.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00>I got a tell from Rampagious&nbsp;(Maelin Starpyre)&nbsp;the other day, telling me how he views the bard "taunt" requirement.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff00></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>Explanation:</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00>- As he explained - and I fully concur -&nbsp;there are situations, where bard is the only _notable_ melee/plate class still standing (wipes or easy LDoN stuff), where we _should_ have some sort of possiblity to out-taunt other classes. This isnt something miraculously new.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#6666ff></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#6666ff>My opinion:</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#6666ff>&gt; Myself, I'm moderately well equipped and I know that when our guild wipes, if I dont die from initial Choruses aggro, the last classes who remain alive are: Monk (FD), Necromancer (FD), Rogue (Escape), Bard (FM). And I've often seen (in Uqua or Txevu) how mobs went to splash every other class to a bloody pulp before it was my turn. That was _without using FM at any time during the fight_.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#6666ff></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#cc6633>My porposal:</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#cc6633>&lt; Tho, what I'd think as not overpowering, would be to add a discipline to bards -&nbsp;which Book would be dropping in High-End&nbsp;only. -&nbsp;and on the same timer/activation that Deftdance disc is used (Meaning = when you use the aggro disc, you CANNOT Deftdance right after). &nbsp;Don`t get me wrong, but ability to out-taunt a cleric trying to camp combined with Deftdance (16 seconds of pure avoidance) would be a bit _too_ powerful.</FONT></DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
