			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Every class in the game can do something to get a lot of aggro in a short time, except bards.&nbsp; I find that in an xp group, if the main tank goes down, there's nothing I can do to save the rest of the group.&nbsp; I have the hp and ac to tank the mobs we fight, but yet I can't get aggro in a pinch.&nbsp; I'm just forced to watch the rest of my group die one by one (usually tank-slower-dps-dps-cleric) and either die myself or fade and wait for rez recovery.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff66>Aanil-Eci wrote:<BR></FONT>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff66>It's 7:30AM Friday morning, and there are currently four Time/GoD geared rangers LFG on my server.&nbsp; You should have no trouble whatsover finding another tank in a pinch without attempting to serve that role yourself.&nbsp; if you find that rangers are inadequate for the task, voice your disapproval of the situation on the ranger boards, and you'll find plenty of agreement.&nbsp; What you won't find is lack of availability.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#66ff66></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is ridiculous.&nbsp; There's no reason I should have to look for&nbsp;a class that has lower hp and ac than I do, but can hold aggro better.&nbsp; I have more hp than all but 1 ranger in my guild, yet I would be the last person to get aggro in a group they were tanking in.&nbsp; Also, groups don't like bards to tank because we lose all our group-enhancing ability at that point because of the need to dot for aggro.&nbsp; It would be nice to be able to do my primary job (haste/overhaste/etc) and also fill in a tanking role which gear-wise I am well-suited for.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The point is, I should be able to get aggro to suit my level of gear.&nbsp; Currently bards are the only class that can't reasonably hold aggro, that makes me behind wizards and enchanters for desirability in a tanking situation.</DIV></DIV>
																		
