<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Kousotsu wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>I find that in an xp group, if the main tank goes down, there's nothing I can do to save the rest of the group.<BR>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Well mez springs to mind but that is often difficult to execute in a multi-player environment or with dotters. This is one of the key issues with the bard class right now, but I do not think taunt is the ideal answer to it. Rather I would prefer to see us get a song of the nature of Shield of Songs that can enable us to go on the defensive in an emergency situation. A song of this nature would definitely not be optimal in a normal xp situation, but could potentially help out in providing an additional raid role for bards, another area we are struggling in.<BR></P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Kousotsu wrote:<BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Also, groups don't like bards to tank because we lose all our group-enhancing ability at that point because of the need to dot for aggro.<BR>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>This sentence highlights precisely why any taunt song should be aimed primarily at low-mid level bards. High level bards do have tools at their disposal to hold aggro at a reduction in their effectiveness. Low level bards, who are more often expected to tank, do not have any way to reliably hold aggro.<BR>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>(-:&nbsp;&nbsp; Zel&nbsp;&nbsp; ;-)<BR></DIV>
																		
